{"word":"ἰσόω","slug":"ἰσόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἰσόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἴσος'><el>ἴσος</el></a>\n<p/><i>to make equal</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>ὄνυχας χεῖράς τε ἰσώσαντο</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> used them in like manner, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be made like</i> or <i>equal to</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}